to = function(t) {

        case "failed":

                ...r,

                fetchFailureReason: t.error
            };

            return {
                ...r,
                fetchStatus: "paused"
            };

                fetchStatus: "fetching"
            };

                status: "error"

                ...r,
                isInvalidated: !0
            };
        case "setState":

                ...t.state
            }

function xb(e, t, n) {

    switch (d) {
    case "top":
        b = {
            x: m,
            y: r.y - i.height
        };
        break;
    case "bottom":
        b = {
            x: m,
            y: r.y + r.height
        };
        break;
    case "right":
        b = {
            x: r.x + r.width,
            y: g
        };
        break;
    case "left":
        b = {
            x: r.x - i.width,
            y: g
        };
        break;
    default:
        b = {
            x: r.x,
            y: r.y
        }

    case "start":
        b[a] -= y * (n && h ? -1 : 1);
        break;
    case "end":
        b[a] += y * (n && h ? -1 : 1);
        break
    }
    return b
}

function d$(e, t) {
    const n = Math.abs(t.top - e.y)
      , r = Math.abs(t.bottom - e.y)
      , i = Math.abs(t.right - e.x)
      , s = Math.abs(t.left - e.x);
    switch (Math.min(n, r, i, s)) {
    case s:
        return "left";
    case i:
        return "right";
    case n:
        return "top";
    case r:
        return "bottom";
    default:
        throw new Error("unreachable")
    }
}
function f$(e, t, n=5) {
    const r = [];
    switch (t) {
    case "top":
        r.push({
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y + n
        }, {
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y + n
        });
        break;
    case "bottom":
        r.push({
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y - n
        }, {
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y - n
        });
        break;
    case "left":
        r.push({
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y - n
        }, {
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y + n
        });
        break;
    case "right":
        r.push({
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y - n
        }, {
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y + n
        });
        break
    }
    return r
}
function h$(e) {
    const {top: t, right: n, bottom: r, left: i} = e;
    return [{
        x: i,
        y: t
    }, {
        x: n,
        y: t
    }, {
        x: n,
        y: r
    }, {
        x: i,
        y: r
    }]
}
function m$(e, t) {
    const {x: n, y: r} = e;
    let i = !1;
    for (let s = 0, a = t.length - 1; s < t.length; a = s++) {
        const u = t[s].x
          , d = t[s].y
          , h = t[a].x
          , m = t[a].y;
        d > r != m > r && n < (h - u) * (r - d) / (m - d) + u && (i = !i)
    }
    return i
}
function p$(e) {
    const t = e.slice();
    return t.sort( (n, r) => n.x < r.x ? -1 : n.x > r.x ? 1 : n.y < r.y ? -1 : n.y > r.y ? 1 : 0),
    g$(t)
}
function g$(e) {
    if (e.length <= 1)
        return e.slice();
    const t = [];
    for (let r = 0; r < e.length; r++) {
        const i = e[r];
        for (; t.length >= 2; ) {
            const s = t[t.length - 1]
              , a = t[t.length - 2];
            if ((s.x - a.x) * (i.y - a.y) >= (s.y - a.y) * (i.x - a.x))
                t.pop();
            else
                break
        }
        t.push(i)
    }
    t.pop();
    const n = [];
    for (let r = e.length - 1; r >= 0; r--) {
        const i = e[r];
        for (; n.length >= 2; ) {
            const s = n[n.length - 1]
              , a = n[n.length - 2];
            if ((s.x - a.x) * (i.y - a.y) >= (s.y - a.y) * (i.x - a.x))
                n.pop();
            else
                break
        }
        n.push(i)
    }
    return n.pop(),
    t.length === 1 && n.length === 1 && t[0].x === n[0].x && t[0].y === n[0].y ? t : t.concat(n)
}
var v$ = TD
  , y$ = ND
  , x$ = PD
  , AD = ED;
const _$ = v$
  , JK = y$
  , eG = x$
  , w$ = p.forwardRef( ({className: e, sideOffset: t=4, ...n}, r) => c.jsx(AD, {
    ref: r,
    sideOffset: t,
    className: pe("z-50 overflow-hidden rounded-md border bg-popover px-3 py-1.5 text-sm text-popover-foreground shadow-md animate-in fade-in-0 zoom-in-95 data-[state=closed]:animate-out data-[state=closed]:fade-out-0 data-[state=closed]:zoom-out-95 data-[side=bottom]:slide-in-from-top-2 data-[side=left]:slide-in-from-right-2 data-[side=right]:slide-in-from-left-2 data-[side=top]:slide-in-from-bottom-2 origin-[--radix-tooltip-content-transform-origin]", e),
    ...n
}));
w$.displayName = AD.displayName;

            }

            console.error("Failed to load favorites from localStorage:", d)
        }
        return new Set
    }
    );
    p.useEffect( () => {
        try {
            localStorage.setItem(Nb, JSON.stringify(Array.from(t)))
        } catch (d) {
            console.error("Failed to save favorites to localStorage:", d)
        }
    }
    , [t]);

        favorites: t,
        addFavorite: d => {
            n(h => {

                return m.add(d),
                m
            }
            )
        }
        ,

            n(h => {
                const m = new Set(h);
                return m.delete(d),
                m
            }
            )
        }

            }
            )
        }

    })

  , Yp = "focusScope.autoFocusOnUnmount"

function M$(e, {select: t=!1}={}) {

            select: t
        }),

}
function A$(e) {
    const t = LD(e)
      , n = Db(t, e)
      , r = Db(t.reverse(), e);
    return [n, r]
}
function LD(e) {
    const t = []
      , n = document.createTreeWalker(e, NodeFilter.SHOW_ELEMENT, {
        acceptNode: r => {
            const i = r.tagName === "INPUT" && r.type === "hidden";
            return r.disabled || r.hidden || i ? NodeFilter.FILTER_SKIP : r.tabIndex >= 0 ? NodeFilter.FILTER_ACCEPT : NodeFilter.FILTER_SKIP
        }
    });
    for (; n.nextNode(); )
        t.push(n.currentNode);
    return t
}
function Db(e, t) {
    for (const n of e)
        if (!R$(n, {
            upTo: t
        }))
            return n
}
function R$(e, {upTo: t}) {
    if (getComputedStyle(e).visibility === "hidden")
        return !0;
    for (; e; ) {
        if (t !== void 0 && e === t)
            return !1;
        if (getComputedStyle(e).display === "none")
            return !0;
        e = e.parentElement
    }
    return !1
}
function j$(e) {
    return e instanceof HTMLInputElement && "select"in e
}
function Eo(e, {select: t=!1}={}) {
    if (e && e.focus) {
        const n = document.activeElement;
        e.focus({
            preventScroll: !0
        }),
        e !== n && j$(e) && t && e.select()
    }
}
var Mb = I$();
function I$() {
    let e = [];
    return {
        add(t) {
            const n = e[0];
            t !== n && (n == null || n.pause()),
            e = Ab(e, t),
            e.unshift(t)
        },
        remove(t) {
            var n;
            e = Ab(e, t),
            (n = e[0]) == null || n.resume()
        }
    }
}
function Ab(e, t) {
    const n = [...e]
      , r = n.indexOf(t);
    return r !== -1 && n.splice(r, 1),
    n
}
function L$(e) {
    return e.filter(t => t.tagName !== "A")
}

const jl = (e, t) => {

    case le.invalid_type:

        break;
    case le.invalid_literal:
        n = `Invalid literal value, expected ${JSON.stringify(e.expected, lt.jsonStringifyReplacer)}`;
        break;
    case le.unrecognized_keys:
        n = `Unrecognized key(s) in object: ${lt.joinValues(e.keys, ", ")}`;

    case le.invalid_union:
        n = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case le.invalid_union_discriminator:

    case le.invalid_enum_value:

    case le.invalid_arguments:

    case le.invalid_date:

    case le.invalid_string:

        break;
    case le.too_small:
        e.type === "array" ? n = `Array must contain ${e.exact ? "exactly" : e.inclusive ?         break;
    case le.too_big:

    const n = (e.toString().split(".")[1] || "").length
      , r = (t.toString().split(".")[1] || "").length
      , i = n > r ? n : r
      , s = parseInt(e.toFixed(i).replace(".", ""))
      , a = parseInt(t.toFixed(i).replace(".", ""));
    return s % a / Math.pow(10, i)
}
class us extends Je {
    constructor() {
        super(...arguments),
        this.min = this.gte,
        this.max = this.lte,
        this.step = this.multipleOf
    }
    _parse(t) {
        if (this._def.coerce && (t.data = Number(t.data)),
        this._getType(t) !== Ce.number) {
            const s = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
            return we(s, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.number,
                received: s.parsedType
            }),
            $e
        }
        let r;
        const i = new In;
        for (const s of this._def.checks)
            s.kind === "int" ? lt.isInteger(t.data) || (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: "integer",
                received: "float",
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : s.kind === "min" ? (s.inclusive ? t.data < s.value : t.data <= s.value) && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.too_small,
                minimum: s.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: s.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : s.kind === "max" ? (s.inclusive ? t.data > s.value : t.data >= s.value) && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.too_big,
                maximum: s.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: s.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : s.kind === "multipleOf" ? B8(t.data, s.value) !== 0 && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.not_multiple_of,
                multipleOf: s.value,
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : s.kind === "finite" ? Number.isFinite(t.data) || (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.not_finite,
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : lt.assertNever(s);
        return {
            status: i.value,
            value: t.data
        }
    }
    gte(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("min", t, !0, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    gt(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("min", t, !1, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    lte(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("max", t, !0, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    lt(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("max", t, !1, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    setLimit(t, n, r, i) {
        return new us({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, {
                kind: t,
                value: n,
                inclusive: r,
                message: Ne.toString(i)
            }]
        })
    }
    _addCheck(t) {
        return new us({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, t]
        })
    }
    int(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "int",
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    positive(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    negative(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    nonpositive(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    nonnegative(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    multipleOf(t, n) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "multipleOf",
            value: t,
            message: Ne.toString(n)
        })
    }
    finite(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "finite",
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    safe(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    get minValue() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "min" && (t === null || n.value > t) && (t = n.value);
        return t
    }
    get maxValue() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "max" && (t === null || n.value < t) && (t = n.value);
        return t
    }
    get isInt() {
        return !!this._def.checks.find(t => t.kind === "int" || t.kind === "multipleOf" && lt.isInteger(t.value))
    }
    get isFinite() {
        let t = null
          , n = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks) {
            if (r.kind === "finite" || r.kind === "int" || r.kind === "multipleOf")
                return !0;
            r.kind === "min" ? (n === null || r.value > n) && (n = r.value) : r.kind === "max" && (t === null || r.value < t) && (t = r.value)
        }
        return Number.isFinite(n) && Number.isFinite(t)
    }
}
us.create = e => new us({
    checks: [],
    typeName: Oe.ZodNumber,
    coerce: (e == null ? void 0 : e.coerce) || !1,
    ...Ze(e)
});
class cs extends Je {
    constructor() {
        super(...arguments),
        this.min = this.gte,
        this.max = this.lte
    }
    _parse(t) {
        if (this._def.coerce)
            try {
                t.data = BigInt(t.data)
            } catch {
                return this._getInvalidInput(t)
            }
        if (this._getType(t) !== Ce.bigint)
            return this._getInvalidInput(t);
        let r;
        const i = new In;
        for (const s of this._def.checks)
            s.kind === "min" ? (s.inclusive ? t.data < s.value : t.data <= s.value) && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.too_small,
                type: "bigint",
                minimum: s.value,
                inclusive: s.inclusive,
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : s.kind === "max" ? (s.inclusive ? t.data > s.value : t.data >= s.value) && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.too_big,
                type: "bigint",
                maximum: s.value,
                inclusive: s.inclusive,
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : s.kind === "multipleOf" ? t.data % s.value !== BigInt(0) && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            we(r, {
                code: le.not_multiple_of,
                multipleOf: s.value,
                message: s.message
            }),
            i.dirty()) : lt.assertNever(s);
        return {
            status: i.value,
            value: t.data
        }
    }
    _getInvalidInput(t) {
        const n = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
        return we(n, {
            code: le.invalid_type,
            expected: Ce.bigint,
            received: n.parsedType
        }),
        $e
    }
    gte(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("min", t, !0, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    gt(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("min", t, !1, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    lte(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("max", t, !0, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    lt(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("max", t, !1, Ne.toString(n))
    }
    setLimit(t, n, r, i) {
        return new cs({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, {
                kind: t,
                value: n,
                inclusive: r,
                message: Ne.toString(i)
            }]
        })
    }
    _addCheck(t) {
        return new cs({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, t]
        })
    }
    positive(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    negative(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    nonpositive(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    nonnegative(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ne.toString(t)
        })
    }
    multipleOf(t, n) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "multipleOf",
            value: t,
            message: Ne.toString(n)
        })
    }
    get minValue() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "min" && (t === null || n.value > t) && (t = n.value);
        return t
    }
    get maxValue() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "max" && (t === null || n.value < t) && (t = n.value);
        return t
    }
}
cs.create = e => {
    var t;
    return new cs({
        checks: [],
        typeName: Oe.ZodBigInt,
        coerce: (t = e == null ? void 0 : e.coerce) !== null && t !== void 0 ? t : !1,
        ...Ze(e)
    })
}

class kc extends Je {
    _parse(t) {
        if (this._def.coerce && (t.data = !!t.data),
        this._getType(t) !== Ce.boolean) {
            const r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
            return we(r, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.boolean,

            }),
            $e

        return Wn(t.data)
    }

class sa extends Je {
    _parse(t) {
        if (this._def.coerce && (t.data = new Date(t.data)),
        this._getType(t) !== Ce.date) {
            const s = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
            return we(s, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.date,
                received: s.parsedType
            }),
            $e
        }
        if (isNaN(t.data.getTime())) {
            const s = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
            return we(s, {
                code: le.invalid_date
            }),
            $e
        }
        const r = new In;
        let i;
        for (const s of this._def.checks)
            s.kind === "min" ? t.data.getTime() < s.value && (i = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, i),
            we(i, {
                code: le.too_small,
                message: s.message,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                minimum: s.value,
                type: "date"
            }),
            r.dirty()) : s.kind === "max" ? t.data.getTime() > s.value && (i = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, i),
            we(i, {
                code: le.too_big,
                message: s.message,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                maximum: s.value,
                type: "date"
            }),
            r.dirty()) : lt.assertNever(s);
        return {
            status: r.value,
            value: new Date(t.data.getTime())
        }
    }
    _addCheck(t) {
        return new sa({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, t]
        })
    }
    min(t, n) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: t.getTime(),
            message: Ne.toString(n)
        })
    }
    max(t, n) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: t.getTime(),
            message: Ne.toString(n)
        })
    }
    get minDate() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "min" && (t === null || n.value > t) && (t = n.value);
        return t != null ? new Date(t) : null
    }
    get maxDate() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "max" && (t === null || n.value < t) && (t = n.value);
        return t != null ? new Date(t) : null
    }
}

class li extends Je {
    _parse(t) {
        const {ctx: n, status: r} = this._processInputParams(t)
          , i = this._def;
        if (n.parsedType !== Ce.array)
            return we(n, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.array,
                received: n.parsedType
            }),
            $e;
        if (i.exactLength !== null) {
            const a = n.data.length > i.exactLength.value
              , u = n.data.length < i.exactLength.value;
            (a || u) && (we(n, {
                code: a ? le.too_big : le.too_small,
                minimum: u ? i.exactLength.value : void 0,
                maximum: a ? i.exactLength.value : void 0,
                type: "array",
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !0,
                message: i.exactLength.message
            }),
            r.dirty())
        }
        if (i.minLength !== null && n.data.length < i.minLength.value && (we(n, {
            code: le.too_small,
            minimum: i.minLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: i.minLength.message
        }),
        r.dirty()),
        i.maxLength !== null && n.data.length > i.maxLength.value && (we(n, {
            code: le.too_big,
            maximum: i.maxLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: i.maxLength.message
        }),
        r.dirty()),
        n.common.async)
            return Promise.all([...n.data].map( (a, u) => i.type._parseAsync(new $i(n,a,n.path,u)))).then(a => In.mergeArray(r, a));
        const s = [...n.data].map( (a, u) => i.type._parseSync(new $i(n,a,n.path,u)));
        return In.mergeArray(r, s)
    }
    get element() {
        return this._def.type
    }
    min(t, n) {
        return new li({
            ...this._def,
            minLength: {
                value: t,
                message: Ne.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    max(t, n) {
        return new li({
            ...this._def,
            maxLength: {
                value: t,
                message: Ne.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    length(t, n) {
        return new li({
            ...this._def,
            exactLength: {
                value: t,
                message: Ne.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    nonempty(t) {
        return this.min(1, t)
    }
}
li.create = (e, t) => new li({
    type: e,
    minLength: null,
    maxLength: null,
    exactLength: null,
    typeName: Oe.ZodArray,
    ...Ze(t)
});
function Ra(e) {
    if (e instanceof Lt) {
        const t = {};
        for (const n in e.shape) {
            const r = e.shape[n];
            t[n] = Fi.create(Ra(r))
        }
        return new Lt({
            ...e._def,
            shape: () => t
        })
    } else
        return e instanceof li ? new li({
            ...e._def,
            type: Ra(e.element)
        }) : e instanceof Fi ? Fi.create(Ra(e.unwrap())) : e instanceof fs ? fs.create(Ra(e.unwrap())) : e instanceof Vi ? Vi.create(e.items.map(t => Ra(t))) : e
}
class Lt extends Je {
    constructor() {
        super(...arguments),
        this._cached = null,
        this.nonstrict = this.passthrough,
        this.augment = this.extend
    }
    _getCached() {
        if (this._cached !== null)
            return this._cached;
        const t = this._def.shape()
          , n = lt.objectKeys(t);
        return this._cached = {
            shape: t,
            keys: n
        }
    }
    _parse(t) {
        if (this._getType(t) !== Ce.object) {
            const h = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
            return we(h, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.object,
                received: h.parsedType
            }),
            $e
        }
        const {status: r, ctx: i} = this._processInputParams(t)
          , {shape: s, keys: a} = this._getCached()
          , u = [];
        if (!(this._def.catchall instanceof _o && this._def.unknownKeys === "strip"))
            for (const h in i.data)
                a.includes(h) || u.push(h);
        const d = [];
        for (const h of a) {
            const m = s[h]
              , g = i.data[h];
            d.push({
                key: {
                    status: "valid",
                    value: h
                },
                value: m._parse(new $i(i,g,i.path,h)),
                alwaysSet: h in i.data
            })
        }
        if (this._def.catchall instanceof _o) {
            const h = this._def.unknownKeys;
            if (h === "passthrough")
                for (const m of u)
                    d.push({
                        key: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: m
                        },
                        value: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: i.data[m]
                        }
                    });
            else if (h === "strict")
                u.length > 0 && (we(i, {
                    code: le.unrecognized_keys,
                    keys: u
                }),
                r.dirty());
            else if (h !== "strip")
                throw new Error("Internal ZodObject error: invalid unknownKeys value.")
        } else {
            const h = this._def.catchall;
            for (const m of u) {
                const g = i.data[m];
                d.push({
                    key: {
                        status: "valid",
                        value: m
                    },
                    value: h._parse(new $i(i,g,i.path,m)),
                    alwaysSet: m in i.data
                })
            }
        }
        return i.common.async ? Promise.resolve().then(async () => {
            const h = [];
            for (const m of d) {
                const g = await m.key
                  , y = await m.value;
                h.push({
                    key: g,
                    value: y,
                    alwaysSet: m.alwaysSet
                })
            }
            return h
        }
        ).then(h => In.mergeObjectSync(r, h)) : In.mergeObjectSync(r, d)
    }
    get shape() {
        return this._def.shape()
    }
    strict(t) {
        return Ne.errToObj,
        new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strict",
            ...t !== void 0 ? {
                errorMap: (n, r) => {
                    var i, s, a, u;
                    const d = (a = (s = (i = this._def).errorMap) === null || s === void 0 ? void 0 : s.call(i, n, r).message) !== null && a !== void 0 ? a : r.defaultError;
                    return n.code === "unrecognized_keys" ? {
                        message: (u = Ne.errToObj(t).message) !== null && u !== void 0 ? u : d
                    } : {
                        message: d
                    }
                }
            } : {}
        })
    }
    strip() {
        return new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strip"
        })
    }
    passthrough() {
        return new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "passthrough"
        })
    }
    extend(t) {
        return new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...t
            })
        })
    }
    merge(t) {
        return new Lt({
            unknownKeys: t._def.unknownKeys,
            catchall: t._def.catchall,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...t._def.shape()
            }),
            typeName: Oe.ZodObject
        })
    }
    setKey(t, n) {
        return this.augment({
            [t]: n
        })
    }
    catchall(t) {
        return new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            catchall: t
        })
    }
    pick(t) {
        const n = {};
        return lt.objectKeys(t).forEach(r => {
            t[r] && this.shape[r] && (n[r] = this.shape[r])
        }
        ),
        new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    omit(t) {
        const n = {};
        return lt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(r => {
            t[r] || (n[r] = this.shape[r])
        }
        ),
        new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    deepPartial() {
        return Ra(this)
    }
    partial(t) {
        const n = {};
        return lt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(r => {
            const i = this.shape[r];
            t && !t[r] ? n[r] = i : n[r] = i.optional()
        }
        ),
        new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    required(t) {
        const n = {};
        return lt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(r => {
            if (t && !t[r])
                n[r] = this.shape[r];
            else {
                let s = this.shape[r];
                for (; s instanceof Fi; )
                    s = s._def.innerType;
                n[r] = s
            }
        }
        ),
        new Lt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    keyof() {
        return dA(lt.objectKeys(this.shape))
    }
}
Lt.create = (e, t) => new Lt({
    shape: () => e,
    unknownKeys: "strip",

class Pc extends Je {
    _parse(t) {
        const {ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(t)
          , r = this._def.options;
        function i(s) {
            for (const u of s)
                if (u.result.status === "valid")
                    return u.result;
            for (const u of s)
                if (u.result.status === "dirty")
                    return n.common.issues.push(...u.ctx.common.issues),
                    u.result;
            const a = s.map(u => new _r(u.ctx.common.issues));
            return we(n, {
                code: le.invalid_union,
                unionErrors: a
            }),
            $e
        }

                        ...n.common,
                        issues: []
                    },
                    parent: null
                };

                    result: await s._parseAsync({
                        data: n.data,
                        path: n.path,
                        parent: a
                    }),
                    ctx: a
                }
            }
            )).then(i);
        {

            const a = [];

                    ...n,
                    common: {
                        ...n.common,
                        issues: []
                    },
                    parent: null
                }
                  , m = d._parseSync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: h
                });
                if (m.status === "valid")
                    return m;
                m.status === "dirty" && !s && (s = {
                    result: m,
                    ctx: h
                }),
                h.common.issues.length && a.push(h.common.issues)
            }
            if (s)
                return n.common.issues.push(...s.ctx.common.issues),
                s.result;

                unionErrors: u
            }),
            $e
        }
    }
    get options() {
        return this._def.options
    }

class Tm extends Je {
    _parse(t) {
        const {ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(t);
        if (n.parsedType !== Ce.object)
            return we(n, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.object,
                received: n.parsedType
            }),
            $e;
        const r = this.discriminator
          , i = n.data[r]
          , s = this.optionsMap.get(i);
        return s ? n.common.async ? s._parseAsync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }) : s._parseSync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }) : (we(n, {
            code: le.invalid_union_discriminator,
            options: Array.from(this.optionsMap.keys()),
            path: [r]
        }),
        $e)
    }
    get discriminator() {
        return this._def.discriminator
    }
    get options() {
        return this._def.options
    }
    get optionsMap() {
        return this._def.optionsMap
    }
    static create(t, n, r) {
        const i = new Map;
        for (const s of n) {
            const a = no(s.shape[t]);
            if (!a.length)
                throw new Error(`A discriminator value for key \`${t}\` could not be extracted from all schema options`);
            for (const u of a) {
                if (i.has(u))
                    throw new Error(`Discriminator property ${String(t)} has duplicate value ${String(u)}`);
                i.set(u, s)
            }
        }
        return new Tm({
            typeName: Oe.ZodDiscriminatedUnion,
            discriminator: t,
            options: n,
            optionsMap: i,
            ...Ze(r)
        })
    }
}
function ny(e, t) {
    const n = oo(e)
      , r = oo(t);
    if (e === t)
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: e
        };
    if (n === Ce.object && r === Ce.object) {
        const i = lt.objectKeys(t)
          , s = lt.objectKeys(e).filter(u => i.indexOf(u) !== -1)
          , a = {
            ...e,
            ...t
        };
        for (const u of s) {
            const d = ny(e[u], t[u]);
            if (!d.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            a[u] = d.data
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: a
        }
    } else if (n === Ce.array && r === Ce.array) {
        if (e.length !== t.length)
            return {
                valid: !1
            };
        const i = [];
        for (let s = 0; s < e.length; s++) {
            const a = e[s]
              , u = t[s]
              , d = ny(a, u);
            if (!d.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            i.push(d.data)
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: i
        }
    } else
        return n === Ce.date && r === Ce.date && +e == +t ? {
            valid: !0,
            data: e
        } : {
            valid: !1
        }
}
class Ec extends Je {

            data: r.data,
            path: r.path,
            parent: r

class Vi extends Je {
    _parse(t) {
        const {status: n, ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(t);
        if (r.parsedType !== Ce.array)
            return we(r, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.array,

                code: le.too_small,
                minimum: this._def.items.length,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                type: "array"
            }),

        !this._def.rest && r.data.length > this._def.items.length && (we(r, {
            code: le.too_big,
            maximum: this._def.items.length,
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            type: "array"
        }),
        n.dirty());

            const d = this._def.items[u] || this._def.rest;
            return d ? d._parse(new $i(r,a,r.path,u)) : null
        }

    }

    }

            rest: t
        })
    }
}

class aa extends Je {
    _parse(t) {
        const {status: n, ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(t);
        if (r.parsedType !== Ce.set)
            return we(r, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.set,
                received: r.parsedType
            }),
            $e;
        const i = this._def;
        i.minSize !== null && r.data.size < i.minSize.value && (we(r, {
            code: le.too_small,
            minimum: i.minSize.value,
            type: "set",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: i.minSize.message
        }),
        n.dirty()),
        i.maxSize !== null && r.data.size > i.maxSize.value && (we(r, {
            code: le.too_big,
            maximum: i.maxSize.value,
            type: "set",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: i.maxSize.message
        }),
        n.dirty());
        const s = this._def.valueType;
        function a(d) {
            const h = new Set;
            for (const m of d) {
                if (m.status === "aborted")
                    return $e;
                m.status === "dirty" && n.dirty(),
                h.add(m.value)
            }
            return {
                status: n.value,
                value: h
            }
        }
        const u = [...r.data.values()].map( (d, h) => s._parse(new $i(r,d,r.path,h)));
        return r.common.async ? Promise.all(u).then(d => a(d)) : a(u)
    }
    min(t, n) {
        return new aa({
            ...this._def,
            minSize: {
                value: t,
                message: Ne.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    max(t, n) {
        return new aa({
            ...this._def,
            maxSize: {
                value: t,
                message: Ne.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    size(t, n) {
        return this.min(t, n).max(t, n)
    }
    nonempty(t) {
        return this.min(1, t)
    }
}

class ll extends Je {
    constructor() {
        super(...arguments),
        this.validate = this.implement
    }
    _parse(t) {
        const {ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(t);
        if (n.parsedType !== Ce.function)
            return we(n, {
                code: le.invalid_type,
                expected: Ce.function,
                received: n.parsedType
            }),
            $e;
        function r(u, d) {
            return Sh({
                data: u,
                path: n.path,
                errorMaps: [n.common.contextualErrorMap, n.schemaErrorMap, bh(), jl].filter(h => !!h),
                issueData: {
                    code: le.invalid_arguments,
                    argumentsError: d
                }
            })
        }
        function i(u, d) {
            return Sh({
                data: u,
                path: n.path,
                errorMaps: [n.common.contextualErrorMap, n.schemaErrorMap, bh(), jl].filter(h => !!h),
                issueData: {
                    code: le.invalid_return_type,
                    returnTypeError: d
                }
            })
        }
        const s = {
            errorMap: n.common.contextualErrorMap
        }
          , a = n.data;
        if (this._def.returns instanceof Ll) {
            const u = this;
            return Wn(async function(...d) {
                const h = new _r([])
                  , m = await u._def.args.parseAsync(d, s).catch(b => {
                    throw h.addIssue(r(d, b)),
                    h
                }
                )
                  , g = await Reflect.apply(a, this, m);
                return await u._def.returns._def.type.parseAsync(g, s).catch(b => {
                    throw h.addIssue(i(g, b)),
                    h
                }
                )
            })
        } else {
            const u = this;
            return Wn(function(...d) {
                const h = u._def.args.safeParse(d, s);
                if (!h.success)
                    throw new _r([r(d, h.error)]);
                const m = Reflect.apply(a, this, h.data)
                  , g = u._def.returns.safeParse(m, s);
                if (!g.success)
                    throw new _r([i(m, g.error)]);
                return g.data
            })
        }
    }
    parameters() {
        return this._def.args
    }
    returnType() {
        return this._def.returns
    }
    args(...t) {
        return new ll({
            ...this._def,
            args: Vi.create(t).rest(Ys.create())
        })
    }
    returns(t) {
        return new ll({
            ...this._def,
            returns: t
        })
    }

        return this.parse(t)
    }
    strictImplement(t) {
        return this.parse(t)
    }
    static create(t, n, r) {
        return new ll({
            args: t || Vi.create([]).rest(Ys.create()),
            returns: n || Ys.create(),
            typeName: Oe.ZodFunction,
            ...Ze(r)
        })
    }

class ds extends Je {
    constructor() {
        super(...arguments),
        Ou.set(this, void 0)
    }
    _parse(t) {
        if (typeof t.data != "string") {
            const n = this._getOrReturnCtx(t)
              , r = this._def.values;
            return we(n, {
                expected: lt.joinValues(r),
                received: n.parsedType,
                code: le.invalid_type
            }),
            $e

        if (Ch(this, Ou) || aA(this, Ou, new Set(this._def.values)),
        !Ch(this, Ou).has(t.data)) {

              , r = this._def.values;

                received: n.data,

            }),
            $e

        return Wn(t.data)

        const t = {};
        for (const n of this._def.values)
            t[n] = n;
        return t
    }

        for (const n of this._def.values)
            t[n] = n;
        return t
    }

        const t = {};
        for (const n of this._def.values)
            t[n] = n;
        return t
    }

        return ds.create(t, {
            ...this._def,
            ...n
        })
    }
    exclude(t, n=this._def) {
        return ds.create(this.options.filter(r => !t.includes(r)), {
            ...this._def,
            ...n
        })
    }

class fi extends Je {
    innerType() {
        return this._def.schema
    }
    sourceType() {
        return this._def.schema._def.typeName === Oe.ZodEffects ? this._def.schema.sourceType() : this._def.schema
    }
    _parse(t) {
        const {status: n, ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(t)
          , i = this._def.effect || null
          , s = {
            addIssue: a => {
                we(r, a),
                a.fatal ? n.abort() : n.dirty()
            }
            ,
            get path() {
                return r.path
            }
        };
        if (s.addIssue = s.addIssue.bind(s),
        i.type === "preprocess") {
            const a = i.transform(r.data, s);
            if (r.common.async)
                return Promise.resolve(a).then(async u => {
                    if (n.value === "aborted")
                        return $e;

                    data: a,
                    path: r.path,
                    parent: r
                });
                return u.status === "aborted" ? $e : u.status === "dirty" || n.value === "dirty" ? Ka(u.value) : u
            }
        }

            const a = u => {

                if (r.common.async)
                    return Promise.resolve(d);
                if (d instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Async refinement encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");
                return u
            }

                    data: r.data,

                a(u.value).then( () => ({
                    status: n.value,
                    value: u.value
                }))))
        }

            if (r.common.async === !1) {

                    data: r.data,
                    path: r.path,
                    parent: r
                });

                    return a;

                if (u instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Asynchronous transform encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");

function n1(e, t, n) {
    for (let r = t; r < e.length; r++) {
        const i = e[r];
        if (i === "\\") {
            r++;
            continue
        }
        if (i === '"')
            return [e.slice(t, r).replace(/\\/g, ""), r + 1];
        if (!n && (i === "," || i === "}"))
            return [e.slice(t, r).replace(/\\/g, ""), r]
    }
    return [e.slice(t).replace(/\\/g, ""), e.length]
}
function $A(e, t=0) {
    const n = [];
    let r = t
      , i = !1;
    for (; r < e.length; ) {
        const s = e[r];
        if (s === ",") {
            (i || r === t) && n.push(""),
            i = !0,
            r++;
            continue
        }
        if (i = !1,
        s === "\\") {
            r += 2;
            continue
        }
        if (s === '"') {
            const [d,h] = n1(e, r + 1, !0);
            n.push(d),
            r = h;
            continue
        }
        if (s === "}")
            return [n, r + 1];
        if (s === "{") {
            const [d,h] = $A(e, r + 1);
            n.push(d),
            r = h;
            continue
        }
        const [a,u] = n1(e, r, !1);
        n.push(a),
        r = u
    }
    return [n, r]
}

const js = class js {
    constructor(t) {

        B(this, "shouldInlineParams", !1);
        this.queryChunks = t
    }
    append(t) {
        return this.queryChunks.push(...t.queryChunks),
        this
    }
    toQuery(t) {
        return $U.startActiveSpan("drizzle.buildSQL", n => {
            const r = this.buildQueryFromSourceParams(this.queryChunks, t);
            return n == null || n.setAttributes({
                "drizzle.query.text": r.sql,
                "drizzle.query.params": JSON.stringify(r.params)
            }),
            r
        }
        )
    }
    buildQueryFromSourceParams(t, n) {
        const r = Object.assign({}, n, {
            inlineParams: n.inlineParams || this.shouldInlineParams,
            paramStartIndex: n.paramStartIndex || {
                value: 0
            }
        })
          , {casing: i, escapeName: s, escapeParam: a, prepareTyping: u, inlineParams: d, paramStartIndex: h} = r;
        return UU(t.map(m => {
            var g;
            if (tn(m, Ir))
                return {
                    sql: m.value.join(""),
                    params: []
                };
            if (tn(m, Mh))
                return {
                    sql: s(m.value),
                    params: []
                };
            if (m === void 0)
                return {
                    sql: "",
                    params: []
                };
            if (Array.isArray(m)) {
                const y = [new Ir("(")];
                for (const [b,C] of m.entries())
                    y.push(C),
                    b < m.length - 1 && y.push(new Ir(", "));
                return y.push(new Ir(")")),
                this.buildQueryFromSourceParams(y, r)
            }
            if (tn(m, js))
                return this.buildQueryFromSourceParams(m.queryChunks, {
                    ...r,
                    inlineParams: d || m.shouldInlineParams
                });
            if (tn(m, gr)) {
                const y = m[gr.Symbol.Schema]
                  , b = m[gr.Symbol.Name];
                return {
                    sql: y === void 0 || m[Dh] ? s(b) : s(y) + "." + s(b),
                    params: []
                }
            }
            if (tn(m, Ol)) {
                const y = i.getColumnCasing(m);
                if (n.invokeSource === "indexes")

                        sql: s(y),
                        params: []
                    };

                return {
                    sql: m.table[Dh] || b === void 0 ? s(m.table[gr.Symbol.Name]) + "." + s(y) : s(b) + "." + s(m.table[gr.Symbol.Name]) + "." + s(y),
                    params: []
                }
            }
            if (tn(m, YA)) {
                const y = m[cl].schema
                  , b = m[cl].name;
                return {
                    sql: y === void 0 || m[cl].isAlias ? s(b) : s(y) + "." + s(b),
                    params: []
                }
            }
            if (tn(m, f_)) {
                if (tn(m.value, Ah))
                    return {
                        sql: a(h.value++, m),
                        params: [m],
                        typings: ["none"]
                    };
                const y = m.value === null ? null : m.encoder.mapToDriverValue(m.value);
                if (tn(y, js))
                    return this.buildQueryFromSourceParams([y], r);
                if (d)
                    return {
                        sql: this.mapInlineParam(y, r),
                        params: []
                    };
                let b = ["none"];
                return u && (b = [u(m.encoder)]),
                {
                    sql: a(h.value++, y),
                    params: [y],
                    typings: b
                }
            }

                sql: a(h.value++, m),
                params: [m],
                typings: ["none"]
            } : tn(m, js.Aliased) && m.fieldAlias !== void 0 ? {
                sql: s(m.fieldAlias),
                params: []
            } : tn(m, d_) ? m._.isWith ? {
                sql: s(m._.alias),
                params: []

                params: []

                sql: s(m.enumName),
                params: []

                params: []
            } : {

                params: [m],
                typings: ["none"]
            }
        }
        ))
    }
    mapInlineParam(t, {escapeString: n}) {
        if (t === null)
            return "null";
        if (typeof t == "number" || typeof t == "boolean")
            return t.toString();
        if (typeof t == "string")
            return n(t);
        if (typeof t == "object") {
            const r = t.toString();
            return n(r === "[object Object]" ? JSON.stringify(t) : r)
        }
        throw new Error("Unexpected param value: " + t)
    }
    getSQL() {
        return this
    }
    as(t) {
        return t === void 0 ? this : new js.Aliased(this,t)
    }
    mapWith(t) {
        return this.decoder = typeof t == "function" ? {
            mapFromDriverValue: t
        } : t,
        this
    }
    inlineParams() {
        return this.shouldInlineParams = !0,
        this
    }
    if(t) {
        return t ? this : void 0
    }
}

    return Math.min(n, Math.max(t, e))

function Ij(e) {
    const t = p.useRef({
        value: e,
        previous: e
    });
    return p.useMemo( () => (t.current.value !== e && (t.current.previous = t.current.value,
    t.current.value = e),
    t.current.previous), [e])
}

function DW(e, t, n, r) {
    const s = ff(n - e)
      , a = ff(r - t)
      , u = Math.sin(s / 2) * Math.sin(s / 2) + Math.cos(ff(e)) * Math.cos(ff(n)) * Math.sin(a / 2) * Math.sin(a / 2);
    return 6371 * (2 * Math.atan2(Math.sqrt(u), Math.sqrt(1 - u)))
}
function ff(e) {
    return e * (Math.PI / 180)
}
function MW() {
    return new Promise( (e, t) => {
        if (!navigator.geolocation) {
            t(new Error("Geolocation is not supported by this browser"));
            return
        }
        navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(n => {
            e({
                latitude: n.coords.latitude,
                longitude: n.coords.longitude
            })
        }
        , n => {
            t(n)
        }
        , {
            enableHighAccuracy: !0,
            timeout: 1e4,
            maximumAge: 0
        })
    }
    )
}

function dq({slotsAvailable: e=4, maxSlots: t=4, size: n="sm", className: r, showLabel: i=!1}) {

      , a = Math.max(1, Math.min(t, 4))
      , u = {
        sm: "w-1.5 h-1.5",
        md: "w-2 h-2",
        lg: "w-2.5 h-2.5"
    }
      , d = {
        sm: "gap-0.5",
        md: "gap-1",
        lg: "gap-1"
    }
      , h = () => s === 1 ? "bg-orange-500" : s === 2 ? "bg-yellow-500" : "bg-emerald-500";
    return c.jsxs("div", {
        className: pe("flex items-center", d[n], r),
        title: `${s} ${s === 1 ? "spot" : "spots"} available`,
        "data-testid": "availability-dots",
        children: [Array.from({
            length: a
        }).map( (m, g) => {
            const y = g < s;
            return c.jsx("div", {
                className: pe("rounded-full transition-colors", u[n], y ? h() : "bg-muted-foreground/30"),
                "data-testid": `dot-${g}-${y ? "filled" : "empty"}`
            }, g)
        }
        ), i && c.jsxs("span", {
            className: "ml-1 text-[10px] text-muted-foreground",
            children: [s, "/", a]
        })]
    })
}

          , ew = I.extend({
            run: function(o, l, f, v) {
                this.stop(),
                this._el = o,
                this._inProgress = !0,
                this._duration = f || .25,
                this._easeOutPower = 1 / Math.max(v || .5, .2),
                this._startPos = ks(o),
                this._offset = l.subtract(this._startPos),
                this._startTime = +new Date,
                this.fire("start"),
                this._animate()
            },
            stop: function() {
                this._inProgress && (this._step(!0),
                this._complete())
            },
            _animate: function() {
                this._animId = te(this._animate, this),
                this._step()
            },
            _step: function(o) {
                var l = +new Date - this._startTime
                  , f = this._duration * 1e3;
                l < f ? this._runFrame(this._easeOut(l / f), o) : (this._runFrame(1),
                this._complete())
            },
            _runFrame: function(o, l) {
                var f = this._startPos.add(this._offset.multiplyBy(o));
                l && f._round(),
                Jt(this._el, f),
                this.fire("step")
            },
            _complete: function() {
                W(this._animId),
                this._inProgress = !1,
                this.fire("end")
            },
            _easeOut: function(o) {
                return 1 - Math.pow(1 - o, this._easeOutPower)
            }
        })
          , at = I.extend({
            options: {

                }

            },

            zoomOut: function(o, l) {

            },
            setZoomAround: function(o, l, f) {

                  , _ = this.getSize().divideBy(2)
                  , N = o instanceof D ? o : this.latLngToContainerPoint(o)
                  , R = N.subtract(_).multiplyBy(1 - 1 / v)
                  , $ = this.containerPointToLatLng(_.add(R));

                })
            },
            _getBoundsCenterZoom: function(o, l) {
                l = l || {},
                o = o.getBounds ? o.getBounds() : de(o);
                var f = q(l.paddingTopLeft || l.padding || [0, 0])
                  , v = q(l.paddingBottomRight || l.padding || [0, 0])
                  , _ = this.getBoundsZoom(o, !1, f.add(v));

                _ === 1 / 0)

                    };

            panTo: function(o, l) {

            },
            panBy: function(o, l) {
                if (o = q(o).round(),
                l = l || {},
                !o.x && !o.y)
                    return this.fire("moveend");
                if (l.animate !== !0 && !this.getSize().contains(o))

                    this;
                if (this._panAnim || (this._panAnim = new ew,
                this._panAnim.on({
                    step: this._onPanTransitionStep,

                } else
                    this._rawPanBy(o),
                    this.fire("move").fire("moveend");

            },
            flyTo: function(o, l, f) {
                if (f = f || {},
                f.animate === !1 || !Me.any3d)
                    return this.setView(o, l, f);
                this._stop();
                var v = this.project(this.getCenter())
                  , _ = this.project(o)
                  , N = this.getSize()
                  , R = this._zoom;
                o = fe(o),
                l = l === void 0 ? R : l;
                var $ = Math.max(N.x, N.y)
                  , K = $ * this.getZoomScale(R, l)
                  , ie = _.distanceTo(v) || 1
                  , be = 1.42
                  , Le = be * be;
                function nt(en) {
                    var Fd = en ? -1 : 1
                      , rO = en ? K : $
                      , iO = K * K - $ * $ + Fd * Le * Le * ie * ie
                      , oO = 2 * rO * Le * ie
                      , lp = iO / oO
                      , jw = Math.sqrt(lp * lp + 1) - lp
                      , sO = jw < 1e-9 ? -18 : Math.log(jw);
                    return sO
                }
                function On(en) {
                    return (Math.exp(en) - Math.exp(-en)) / 2
                }
                function pn(en) {
                    return (Math.exp(en) + Math.exp(-en)) / 2
                }
                function Mr(en) {
                    return On(en) / pn(en)
                }
                var Gn = nt(0);
                function ka(en) {
                    return $ * (pn(Gn) / pn(Gn + be * en))
                }
                function JL(en) {
                    return $ * (pn(Gn) * Mr(Gn + be * en) - On(Gn)) / Le
                }
                function eO(en) {
                    return 1 - Math.pow(1 - en, 1.5)
                }
                var tO = Date.now()
                  , Aw = (nt(1) - Gn) / be
                  , nO = f.duration ? 1e3 * f.duration : 1e3 * Aw * .8;
                function Rw() {
                    var en = (Date.now() - tO) / nO
                      , Fd = eO(en) * Aw;
                    en <= 1 ? (this._flyToFrame = te(Rw, this),
                    this._move(this.unproject(v.add(_.subtract(v).multiplyBy(JL(Fd) / ie)), R), this.getScaleZoom($ / ka(Fd), R), {
                        flyTo: !0
                    })) : this._move(o, l)._moveEnd(!0)
                }
                return this._moveStart(!0, f.noMoveStart),
                Rw.call(this),
                this
            },
            flyToBounds: function(o, l) {
                var f = this._getBoundsCenterZoom(o, l);
                return this.flyTo(f.center, f.zoom, l)
            },
            setMaxBounds: function(o) {

            panInside: function(o, l) {

                }

            },
            invalidateSize: function(o) {

                    return this;
                o = i({
                    animate: !1,

                    animate: !0
                } : o);

                }))
            },
            stop: function() {
                return this.setZoom(this._limitZoom(this._zoom)),

            },
            locate: function(o) {

                    timeout: 1e4,

                }, o),
                !("geolocation"in navigator))
                    return this._handleGeolocationError({
                        code: 0,

                    }),

                this
            },
            stopLocate: function() {
                return navigator.geolocation && navigator.geolocation.clearWatch && navigator.geolocation.clearWatch(this._locationWatchId),
                this._locateOptions && (this._locateOptions.setView = !1),

            },
            _handleGeolocationError: function(o) {
                if (this._container._leaflet_id) {
                    var l = o.code
                      , f = o.message || (l === 1 ? "permission denied" : l === 2 ? "position unavailable" : "timeout");
                    this._locateOptions.setView && !this._loaded && this.fitWorld(),
                    this.fire("locationerror", {
                        code: l,
                        message: "Geolocation error: " + f + "."
                    })
                }
            },

                        this.setView(v, N.maxZoom ? Math.min(R, N.maxZoom) : R)
                    }

                        latlng: v,
                        bounds: _,
                        timestamp: o.timestamp
                    };
                    for (var K in o.coords)
                        typeof o.coords[K] == "number" && ($[K] = o.coords[K]);
                    this.fire("locationfound", $)
                }
            },

            _findEventTargets: function(o, l) {

            },

        var tw = Kr.extend({

        function ow(o, l) {

        function TL(o, l) {

        function uw(o, l, f, v, _) {

        function Nd(o, l, f, v, _) {
            var N = l.x - o.x, R = l.y - o.y, $ = v.min, K = v.max, ie, be;
            return f & 8 ? (ie = o.x + N * (K.y - o.y) / R,
            be = K.y) : f & 4 ? (ie = o.x + N * ($.y - o.y) / R,
            be = $.y) : f & 2 ? (ie = K.x,
            be = o.y + R * (K.x - o.x) / N) : f & 1 && (ie = $.x,
            be = o.y + R * ($.x - o.x) / N),
            new D(ie,be,_)
        }
        function Ps(o, l) {
            var f = 0;
            return o.x < l.min.x ? f |= 1 : o.x > l.max.x && (f |= 2),
            o.y < l.min.y ? f |= 4 : o.y > l.max.y && (f |= 8),
            f
        }
        function NL(o, l) {
            var f = l.x - o.x
              , v = l.y - o.y;
            return f * f + v * v
        }
        function lu(o, l, f, v) {
            var _ = l.x, N = l.y, R = f.x - _, $ = f.y - N, K = R * R + $ * $, ie;
            return K > 0 && (ie = ((o.x - _) * R + (o.y - N) * $) / K,
            ie > 1 ? (_ = f.x,
            N = f.y) : ie > 0 && (_ += R * ie,
            N += $ * ie)),
            R = o.x - _,
            $ = o.y - N,
            v ? R * R + $ * $ : new D(_,N)
        }
        function Dr(o) {
            return !k(o[0]) || typeof o[0][0] != "object" && typeof o[0][0] < "u"
        }
        function cw(o) {
            return console.warn("Deprecated use of _flat, please use L.LineUtil.isFlat instead."),
            Dr(o)
        }
        function dw(o, l) {
            var f, v, _, N, R, $, K, ie;
            if (!o || o.length === 0)
                throw new Error("latlngs not passed");
            Dr(o) || (console.warn("latlngs are not flat! Only the first ring will be used"),
            o = o[0]);
            var be = fe([0, 0])
              , Le = de(o)
              , nt = Le.getNorthWest().distanceTo(Le.getSouthWest()) * Le.getNorthEast().distanceTo(Le.getNorthWest());
            nt < 1700 && (be = ep(o));
            var On = o.length
              , pn = [];
            for (f = 0; f < On; f++) {
                var Mr = fe(o[f]);
                pn.push(l.project(fe([Mr.lat - be.lat, Mr.lng - be.lng])))
            }
            for (f = 0,
            v = 0; f < On - 1; f++)
                v += pn[f].distanceTo(pn[f + 1]) / 2;
            if (v === 0)
                ie = pn[0];
            else
                for (f = 0,
                N = 0; f < On - 1; f++)
                    if (R = pn[f],
                    $ = pn[f + 1],
                    _ = R.distanceTo($),
                    N += _,
                    N > v) {
                        K = (N - v) / _,
                        ie = [$.x - K * ($.x - R.x), $.y - K * ($.y - R.y)];
                        break
                    }
            var Gn = l.unproject(q(ie));
            return fe([Gn.lat + be.lat, Gn.lng + be.lng])
        }

          , np = {
            project: function(o) {
                return new D(o.lng,o.lat)

          , rp = {
            R: 6378137,
            R_MINOR: 6356752314245179e-9,
            bounds: new ae([-2003750834279e-5, -1549657073972e-5],[2003750834279e-5, 1876465623138e-5]),
            project: function(o) {
                var l = Math.PI / 180
                  , f = this.R
                  , v = o.lat * l
                  , _ = this.R_MINOR / f
                  , N = Math.sqrt(1 - _ * _)
                  , R = N * Math.sin(v)
                  , $ = Math.tan(Math.PI / 4 - v / 2) / Math.pow((1 - R) / (1 + R), N / 2);
                return v = -f * Math.log(Math.max($, 1e-10)),
                new D(o.lng * l * f,v)
            },
            unproject: function(o) {
                for (var l = 180 / Math.PI, f = this.R, v = this.R_MINOR / f, _ = Math.sqrt(1 - v * v), N = Math.exp(-o.y / f), R = Math.PI / 2 - 2 * Math.atan(N), $ = 0, K = .1, ie; $ < 15 && Math.abs(K) > 1e-7; $++)
                    ie = _ * Math.sin(R),
                    ie = Math.pow((1 - ie) / (1 + ie), _ / 2),
                    K = Math.PI / 2 - 2 * Math.atan(N * ie) - R,
                    R += K;
                return new oe(R * l,o.x * l / f)
            }
        }

        var ip = Ed.extend({
            initialize: function(o, l, f) {

                    radius: l
                })),

            _project: function() {
                var o = this._latlng.lng
                  , l = this._latlng.lat
                  , f = this._map
                  , v = f.options.crs;
                if (v.distance === Te.distance) {
                    var _ = Math.PI / 180
                      , N = this._mRadius / Te.R / _
                      , R = f.project([l + N, o])
                      , $ = f.project([l - N, o])
                      , K = R.add($).divideBy(2)
                      , ie = f.unproject(K).lat
                      , be = Math.acos((Math.cos(N * _) - Math.sin(l * _) * Math.sin(ie * _)) / (Math.cos(l * _) * Math.cos(ie * _))) / _;

                    this._point = K.subtract(f.getPixelOrigin()),
                    this._radius = isNaN(be) ? 0 : K.x - f.project([ie, o - be]).x,
                    this._radiusY = K.y - R.y
                } else {
                    var Le = v.unproject(v.project(this._latlng).subtract([this._mRadius, 0]));
                    this._point = f.latLngToLayerPoint(this._latlng),
                    this._radius = this._point.x - f.latLngToLayerPoint(Le).x
                }
                this._updateBounds()
            }

                    N = 0; N < _; N++)

            _clipPoints: function() {

        function Dd(o, l) {
            var f = o.type === "Feature" ? o.geometry : o, v = f ? f.coordinates : null, _ = [], N = l && l.pointToLayer, R = l && l.coordsToLatLng || op, $, K, ie, be;
            if (!v && !f)
                return null;
            switch (f.type) {
            case "Point":
                return $ = R(v),
                mw(N, o, $, l);
            case "MultiPoint":
                for (ie = 0,
                be = v.length; ie < be; ie++)
                    $ = R(v[ie]),
                    _.push(mw(N, o, $, l));
                return new Ki(_);
            case "LineString":
            case "MultiLineString":
                return K = Md(v, f.type === "LineString" ? 0 : 1, R),
                new Gi(K,l);
            case "Polygon":
            case "MultiPolygon":
                return K = Md(v, f.type === "Polygon" ? 1 : 2, R),
                new ba(K,l);
            case "GeometryCollection":
                for (ie = 0,
                be = f.geometries.length; ie < be; ie++) {
                    var Le = Dd({
                        geometry: f.geometries[ie],
                        type: "Feature",
                        properties: o.properties
                    }, l);
                    Le && _.push(Le)
                }
                return new Ki(_);
            case "FeatureCollection":
                for (ie = 0,
                be = f.features.length; ie < be; ie++) {
                    var nt = Dd(f.features[ie], l);
                    nt && _.push(nt)
                }
                return new Ki(_);
            default:
                throw new Error("Invalid GeoJSON object.")
            }
        }
        function mw(o, l, f, v) {

        }
        function op(o) {

                            l = f[v];
                            break

                        return !1;

            },

            },
            _resetView: function(o) {

            },

            },

            _update: function(o) {

                            throw new Error("Attempted to load an infinite number of tiles");

            _isValidTile: function(o) {

                        return !1
                }

                })
            },
            _tileReady: function(o, l, f) {

                });

            },

            _noTilesToLoad: function() {

                    if (!this._tiles[o].loaded)

            }

            _initContainer: function() {

                We(o, "mousemove", this._onMouseMove, this),
                We(o, "click dblclick mousedown mouseup contextmenu", this._onClick, this),
                We(o, "mouseout", this._handleMouseOut, this),
                o._leaflet_disable_events = !0,
                this._ctx = o.getContext("2d")
            },
            _destroyContainer: function() {
                W(this._redrawRequest),
                delete this._ctx,
                Rt(this._container),
                Ct(this._container),
                delete this._container
            },
            _updatePaths: function() {
                if (!this._postponeUpdatePaths) {
                    var o;
                    this._redrawBounds = null;
                    for (var l in this._layers)
                        o = this._layers[l],
                        o._update();
                    this._redraw()
                }
            },
            _update: function() {
                if (!(this._map._animatingZoom && this._bounds)) {
                    Qi.prototype._update.call(this);
                    var o = this._bounds
                      , l = this._container
                      , f = o.getSize()
                      , v = Me.retina ? 2 : 1;
                    Jt(l, o.min),
                    l.width = v * f.x,

                    l.style.height = f.y + "px",

                    this._ctx.translate(-o.min.x, -o.min.y),
                    this.fire("update")
                }
            },
            _reset: function() {
                Qi.prototype._reset.call(this),
                this._postponeUpdatePaths && (this._postponeUpdatePaths = !1,
                this._updatePaths())
            },
            _initPath: function(o) {
                this._updateDashArray(o),
                this._layers[d(o)] = o;
                var l = o._order = {
                    layer: o,
                    prev: this._drawLast,
                    next: null
                };
                this._drawLast && (this._drawLast.next = l),
                this._drawLast = l,
                this._drawFirst = this._drawFirst || this._drawLast
            },
            _addPath: function(o) {
                this._requestRedraw(o)
            },
            _removePath: function(o) {
                var l = o._order
                  , f = l.next
                  , v = l.prev;
                f ? f.prev = v : this._drawLast = v,
                v ? v.next = f : this._drawFirst = f,
                delete o._order,
                delete this._layers[d(o)],
                this._requestRedraw(o)
            },
            _updatePath: function(o) {
                this._extendRedrawBounds(o),
                o._project(),
                o._update(),
                this._requestRedraw(o)
            },
            _updateStyle: function(o) {
                this._updateDashArray(o),
                this._requestRedraw(o)
            },
            _updateDashArray: function(o) {
                if (typeof o.options.dashArray == "string") {
                    var l = o.options.dashArray.split(/[, ]+/), f = [], v, _;
                    for (_ = 0; _ < l.length; _++) {
                        if (v = Number(l[_]),
                        isNaN(v))
                            return;
                        f.push(v)
                    }
                    o.options._dashArray = f
                } else
                    o.options._dashArray = o.options.dashArray
            },
            _requestRedraw: function(o) {
                this._map && (this._extendRedrawBounds(o),
                this._redrawRequest = this._redrawRequest || te(this._redraw, this))
            },
            _extendRedrawBounds: function(o) {

                    var l = (o.options.weight || 0) + 1;
                    this._redrawBounds = this._redrawBounds || new ae,
                    this._redrawBounds.extend(o._pxBounds.min.subtract([l, l])),
                    this._redrawBounds.extend(o._pxBounds.max.add([l, l]))
                }
            },
            _redraw: function() {
                this._redrawRequest = null,
                this._redrawBounds && (this._redrawBounds.min._floor(),
                this._redrawBounds.max._ceil()),
                this._clear(),
                this._draw(),
                this._redrawBounds = null
            },
            _clear: function() {
                var o = this._redrawBounds;
                if (o) {
                    var l = o.getSize();
                    this._ctx.clearRect(o.min.x, o.min.y, l.x, l.y)

                    this._ctx.save(),
                    this._ctx.setTransform(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0),
                    this._ctx.clearRect(0, 0, this._container.width, this._container.height),
                    this._ctx.restore()
            },
            _draw: function() {
                var o, l = this._redrawBounds;
                if (this._ctx.save(),
                l) {
                    var f = l.getSize();
                    this._ctx.beginPath(),
                    this._ctx.rect(l.min.x, l.min.y, f.x, f.y),
                    this._ctx.clip()

                this._drawing = !0;
                for (var v = this._drawFirst; v; v = v.next)
                    o = v.layer,
                    (!l || o._pxBounds && o._pxBounds.intersects(l)) && o._updatePath();
                this._drawing = !1,
                this._ctx.restore()
            },
            _updatePoly: function(o, l) {
                if (this._drawing) {
                    var f, v, _, N, R = o._parts, $ = R.length, K = this._ctx;
                    if ($) {
                        for (K.beginPath(),
                        f = 0; f < $; f++) {
                            for (v = 0,
                            _ = R[f].length; v < _; v++)
                                N = R[f][v],
                                K[v ? "lineTo" : "moveTo"](N.x, N.y);
                            l && K.closePath()
                        }
                        this._fillStroke(K, o)
                    }
                }
            },
            _updateCircle: function(o) {
                if (!(!this._drawing || o._empty())) {
                    var l = o._point
                      , f = this._ctx
                      , v = Math.max(Math.round(o._radius), 1)
                      , _ = (Math.max(Math.round(o._radiusY), 1) || v) / v;
                    _ !== 1 && (f.save(),
                    f.scale(1, _)),
                    f.beginPath(),
                    f.arc(l.x, l.y / _, v, 0, Math.PI * 2, !1),
                    _ !== 1 && f.restore(),
                    this._fillStroke(f, o)
                }
            },
            _fillStroke: function(o, l) {
                var f = l.options;
                f.fill && (o.globalAlpha = f.fillOpacity,
                o.fillStyle = f.fillColor || f.color,
                o.fill(f.fillRule || "evenodd")),
                f.stroke && f.weight !== 0 && (o.setLineDash && o.setLineDash(l.options && l.options._dashArray || []),

                o.lineWidth = f.weight,
                o.strokeStyle = f.color,
                o.lineCap = f.lineCap,
                o.lineJoin = f.lineJoin,
                o.stroke())
            },
            _onClick: function(o) {
                for (var l = this._map.mouseEventToLayerPoint(o), f, v, _ = this._drawFirst; _; _ = _.next)
                    f = _.layer,

                this._fireEvent(v ? [v] : !1, o)
            },
            _onMouseMove: function(o) {
                if (!(!this._map || this._map.dragging.moving() || this._map._animatingZoom)) {
                    var l = this._map.mouseEventToLayerPoint(o);
                    this._handleMouseHover(o, l)
                }
            },
            _handleMouseOut: function(o) {

                l && (qt(this._container, "leaflet-interactive"),
                this._fireEvent([l], o, "mouseout"),
                this._hoveredLayer = null,
                this._mouseHoverThrottled = !1)
            },
            _handleMouseHover: function(o, l) {

                    for (var f, v, _ = this._drawFirst; _; _ = _.next)
                        f = _.layer,
                        f.options.interactive && f._containsPoint(l) && (v = f);
                    v !== this._hoveredLayer && (this._handleMouseOut(o),

                    this._fireEvent([v], o, "mouseover"),
                    this._hoveredLayer = v)),
                    this._fireEvent(this._hoveredLayer ? [this._hoveredLayer] : !1, o),
                    this._mouseHoverThrottled = !0,
                    setTimeout(a(function() {
                        this._mouseHoverThrottled = !1
                    }, this), 32)
                }
            },
            _fireEvent: function(o, l, f) {
                this._map._fireDOMEvent(l, f || l.type, o)
            },
            _bringToFront: function(o) {
                var l = o._order;
                if (l) {
                    var f = l.next
                      , v = l.prev;
                    if (f)
                        f.prev = v;
                    else
                        return;
                    v ? v.next = f : f && (this._drawFirst = f),
                    l.prev = this._drawLast,
                    this._drawLast.next = l,
                    l.next = null,
                    this._drawLast = l,
                    this._requestRedraw(o)
                }
            },
            _bringToBack: function(o) {
                var l = o._order;
                if (l) {
                    var f = l.next
                      , v = l.prev;
                    if (v)
                        v.next = f;

                }
            }

        var Nw = wi.extend({
            addHooks: function() {

                    this._draggable = new bo(o._mapPane,o._container),
                    this._draggable.on({
                        dragstart: this._onDragStart,

            },

            },

                return this._draggable && this._draggable._moving
            },
            _onDragStart: function() {
                var o = this._map;
                if (o._stop(),
                this._map.options.maxBounds && this._map.options.maxBoundsViscosity) {
                    var l = de(this._map.options.maxBounds);
                    this._offsetLimit = V(this._map.latLngToContainerPoint(l.getNorthWest()).multiplyBy(-1), this._map.latLngToContainerPoint(l.getSouthEast()).multiplyBy(-1).add(this._map.getSize())),

                } else

                o.fire("movestart").fire("dragstart"),
                o.options.inertia && (this._positions = [],
                this._times = [])
            },
            _onDrag: function(o) {
